DeleteBook - Class in bcu.cmp5332.librarysystem.commands
Deletes a book from the library.
It is an implementation of the Command interface and its execute method deletes the given book from the system.
It is created and executed by the CommandParser when the "deletebook" command is given by the user.
The class has a constructor to intialise the fields needed to execute the command.
DeleteBook(int) - Constructor for class bcu.cmp5332.librarysystem.commands.DeleteBook
Initialises DeleteBook using the necessary variables.

displayBooks() - Method in class bcu.cmp5332.librarysystem.gui.MainWindow
Creates a table view of all the books in the library database that are not removed("hidden").
It displays column headers and multiple rows of book instances.
The last column "Borrower Details" opens pop up window if it specifically says "View Borrower Details".
